reviewText: Early Victor Saville direction of Jessie Matthews.  It's a little rough but great example of Jessie on her way to becoming Britain's greatest forgotton star

Jessie Matthews is always a joy to watch and in addition this omnibus movie includes many of the iconic British stars of the 30's and 40's. One of the earliest and most entertaining omnibus movies. The restored print whilst not pristine is imminently watchable.
